<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<h2>Introduction</h2>

<p>Back of the Plane operates Back of the Plane.com. It is Back of the Plane's policy to respect your privacy regarding any information we may collect while operating our Web sites.

<h2>Web site Visitors</h2>

<p>Like most Web site operators, Back of the Plane collects non-personally-identifying information of the sort that web browsers and servers typically make available, such as the browser type, language preference, referring site, and the date and time of each visitor request. Back of the Plane's purpose in collecting non-personally-identifying information is to better understand how Back of the Plane's visitors use its Web site. From time to time, Back of the Plane may release non-personally-identifying information in the aggregate, e.g., by publishing a report on trends in the usage of its Web site.</p>

<p>Back of the Plane also collects potentially personally-identifying information like Internet Protocol (IP) addresses. Back of the Plane does not use such information to identify its visitors, however, and does not disclose such information, other than under the same circumstances that it uses and discloses personally-identifying information, as described below.</p>

<h2>Gathering of Personally-Identifying Information</h2>

<p>Certain visitors to Back of the Plane's Web sites choose to interact with Back of the Plane in ways that require Back of the Plane to gather personally-identifying information. The amount and type of information that Back of the Plane gathers depends on the nature of the interaction. For example, we ask visitors who PERFORM AN ACTION at Back of the Plane to provide CERTAIN DETAILS. Those who engage in transactions with Back of the Plane – by DOING SOMETHING, for example – are asked to provide additional information, including as necessary the personal and financial information required to process those transactions. In each case, Back of the Plane collects such information only insofar as is necessary or appropriate to fulfill the purpose of the visitor's interaction with Back of the Plane. Back of the Plane does not disclose personally-identifying information other than as described below. And visitors can always refuse to supply personally-identifying information, with the caveat that it may prevent them from engaging in certain Web site-related activities.</p>

<h2>Aggregated Statistics</h2>

<p>Back of the Plane may collect statistics about the behavior of visitors to its Web sites. For instance, Back of the Plane may monitor the most popular parts of the Back of the Plane site. Back of the Plane may display this information publicly or provide it to others. However, Back of the Plane does not disclose personally-identifying information other than as described below.</p>

<h2>Protection of Certain Personally-Identifying Information</h2>

<p>Back of the Plane discloses potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information only to those of its employees, contractors and affiliated organizations that (i) need to know that information in order to process it on Back of the Plane's behalf or to provide services available at Back of the Plane's Web sites, and (ii) that have agreed not to disclose it to others. Some of those employees, contractors and affiliated organizations may be located outside of your home country; by using Back of the Plane's Web sites, you consent to the transfer of such information to them. Back of the Plane will not rent or sell potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information to anyone. Other than to its employees, contractors and affiliated organizations, as described above, Back of the Plane discloses potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information only when required to do so by law, or when Back of the Plane believes in good faith that disclosure is reasonably necessary to protect the property or rights of Back of the Plane, third parties or the public at large. If you are a registered user of a Back of the Plane Web site and have supplied your email address, Back of the Plane may occasionally send you an email to tell you about new features, solicit your feedback, or just keep you up to date with what's going on with Back of the Plane and our products. We primarily use our OTHER METHODS, SUCH AS WEB SITE OR BLOGS to communicate this type of information, so we expect to keep this type of email to a minimum. If you send us a request (for example via a support email or via one of our feedback mechanisms), we reserve the right to publish it in order to help us clarify or respond to your request or to help us support other users. Back of the Plane takes all measures reasonably necessary to protect against the unauthorized access, use, alteration or destruction of potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information.</p>

<h2>Cookies</h2>

<p>A cookie is a string of information that a Web site stores on a visitor's computer, and that the visitor's browser provides to the Web site each time the visitor returns. Back of the Plane uses cookies to help Back of the Plane identify and track visitors, their usage of Back of the Plane Web site, and their Web site access preferences. Back of the Plane visitors who do not wish to have cookies placed on their computers should set their browsers to refuse cookies before using Back of the Plane's Web sites, with the drawback that certain features of Back of the Plane's Web sites may not function properly without the aid of cookies.</p>

<h2>Privacy Policy Changes</h2>

<p>Although most changes are likely to be minor, Back of the Plane may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in Back of the Plane's sole discretion. Back of the Plane encourages visitors to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.</p>
